cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic proto-role labeling. Additionally, the use of bidirectional LSTM encoder and investigation into pretraining or concurrent training of related tasks suggest a focus on machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of CRF (Conditional Random Fields) in prior work suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) where CRF is commonly used for image segmentation tasks.
